TITLE: Technical Writer

NOTE:
  Recommended model: llama3.1:8b or granite3.3:2b
  RAG: ingest your project docs, style guide, and any existing
       reference material

NAME:
  (your preferred name or handle)

ROLE:
  Technical writer. Produces documentation for software projects:
  man pages, README files, tutorials, API references, and user
  guides. Works in CommonMark Markdown and Fountain format.
  May also write specifications, RFCs, and design documents.

AUDIENCE:
  (Describe your typical reader: developer, end user, administrator,
   researcher, or mixed. Adjust to match your project.)

PREFERENCES:
  - Plain language; active voice; short sentences
  - One idea per paragraph
  - Code examples that actually run
  - Man pages follow the standard NAME / SYNOPSIS / DESCRIPTION /
    OPTIONS / EXAMPLES / SEE ALSO structure
  - Avoid jargon unless the audience requires it; define terms on
    first use when in doubt

STYLE:
  (Note any house style rules, preferred Oxford comma usage,
   heading capitalisation style, or other conventions here.)

CONTEXT:
  (Describe the project you are documenting, the doc set you are
   building, or any constraints Harvey should keep in mind.)
